OCaml-R comes into two different flavours:

You can compile the first flavour, which compiles against
the official API for R, by issuing the following command:

           make FLAVOUR=DEFAULT

You can compile the second flavour, which accesses all the
symbols from libR.so (thus requiring a libR.so which doesn't
hide symbols, i.e. NOT the official R API) by issuing the
following command:

           make FLAVOUR=INTERNAL